packagedElement.name: Party Reference Data Directory BOM SD

ownedComment.body:
A written authorization that transfers specific rights from a party to another party.
Document that transfers specific rights from a party to another party. ISO20022

An agreement that authorises a party (holding party) to act on behalf of a principal party.
Authorisation given by an issuing party to a holder party to act on the issuer's behalf. (ISO20022)
Written authorization and/or command by a person, group, or organization (the 'mandator') to another (the 'mandatary') to take a certain course of action. (Business Dictionary)
An agreement that outlines the terms and conditions of the relationship between the two or more parties. An agreement has arrangements which are the cause of the relationship.
A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.

A party represents an autonomous entity in which a bank has a business interest. It has a legal definition and identity. A party is a Person, Organization, (a proposed definition for BIAN BOM adapted from BIAN Party Working Group)
- Entity involved in an activity. (ISO20022)
Name by which a party is known and which is usually used to identify that party. (ISO20022)
Specifies the type of party in different business contexts. (ISO20022)
A place to locate a person.

An entry in a directory.
A registry of items recording key reference information and properties relating to each. (BIAN SL)
An entry in a Party Reference Data Directory
The definition of an addressable space/position both in real and virtual environments with associated uses and entitlements
A description of the property, particularly if it has landmark characteristics.
Key dates associated with the directory entry (e.g. open date, refresh date).
The tracked status (e.g. under construction or repair, inhabited, vacant).
Type of location (e.g. building, point of interest, virtual location/device).
The planning or zoning status (e.g. residential, commercial, industrial).
The general purpose and neighborhood of the property (e.g. residential, industrial, commercial).
The construction approach for a property at the location (e.g. era and architecture as might be used in valuation).
The type of occupancy (e.g. residency, business, retail, entertainment).
The estimated (book) value of the property at the location - rental and purchase as appropriate.
An indication of the size or scale of the property where appropriate (e.g. 4 bedroom, 600 seat auditorium, 40 cover restaurant).
A registry to record some specific items.
A directory that maintains party reference data
structure/make-up of an organizational entity
Sector of business of the organisation, for example, pharmaceutical. (ISO20022)
Date and time at which a given organisation was officially registered. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a social security agency. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a license authority to a driver's license. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a passport authority to a passport. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a national authority to an identity card. (ISO20022)
Number assigned to an employer by a registration authority. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a tax authority to an entity. (ISO20022)
Number assigned by a national registration authority to an entity. In Singapore this is known as the NRIC. (ISO20022)
An identifier for the Legal Entity in a business registry in the jurisdiction of legal registration, or in the appropriate registration authority. (ISO20022)
Address which is accessed by electronic means. ISO20022
Information that locates and identifies a specific address. ISO20022
Collection of information that identifies a phone address. ISO20022
A social network such as Facebook, Twitter, etc.
Nation with its own government. ISO20022
Regulatory authority of the country. (ISO20022)
A specific role of a specific Party in the specific Customer Relationship.
A Functional Classification Hierarchy that distinguishes between roles/responsibilities involved in the customer relationship like Customer, Supplier/Bank, the relationship manager.

A specific relationship between a specific Bank (= party acting as a supplier of banking services) and one or more other involved parties acting as (potential) consumers of banking services as agreed in one or more banking product or service offerings and/or agreements.
A place to locate a party.

The use a party makes of a location
e.g. domicile, correspondence address
Number, physical or virtual address, used for communication.
Information to support Know Your Customer (KYC) processes. (ISO20022)

Specifies if due diligence checks on the political exposure of the investor have been carried out and whether these checks are national or foreign. (A politically exposed person is someone who has been entrusted with a prominent public function, or an individual who is closely related to such a person.) ISO20022
Specifies the level of salary. (ISO20022)
Indicates if the employment of the person has been terminated. (ISO20022)
Indicates if the person has family medical insurance coverage available. (ISO20022)
Highest level of education attained.
Name of the occupation or job of a person. (ISO20022)
Human entity, as distinguished from a corporate entity (which is sometimes referred to as an 'artificial person'). ISO20022
Residential status of an individual, for example, non-permanent resident. (ISO20022)
Date on which a person is born. (ISO20022)
Specifies the country where a person was born or is legally accepted as belonging to the country. (ISO20022)
The religious identification of the person.

A formal or informal common understanding between two or more (legal competent) parties concerning one or more subject matters expressed in a set of arrangements, terms and conditions. (adapted from Legal System and FIBO)
Date on which the agreement was signed by all parties. (ISO20022)

Specifies the category of agreement. Agreement type is very often referred to product. But, the term product does not cover all kinds of agreements. An Agreement can be subtyped from the perspective of various aspects of interest. One can classify the agreement from the perspective of format type (e.g., verbal agreement, written agreement). Other one can classify agreement based on duration like short-term agreement or long-term agreement.
Period during which the agreement is valid
LifecycleStatus of agreement (e.g., potential, offered, confirmed, completed, signed, terminated)
The identifier of agreement like Agreement Number, Contract Number, Contract Registration Number, etc.

A characteristic of agreement which refers to 1) LifecycleDate of agreement (e.g., SignedDate, TerminatedDate, FulfilledDate) OR 2) ArrangedDate of agreement (e.g., StartingDate, EndingDate, ValidityPeriod, EffectiveDate).
A Place to locate an organisation.

A relationship between two or more parties; the parties involved are specified in terms of the roles they play in the relationship.
A Party Relationship is a connection between an instance of a Party and two or more instances of associated objects in the relationship.
Contact person for a customer in a relationship with a financial institution.
Legal Entity Identifier is a code allocated to a party as described in ISO 17442 "Financial Services - Legal Entity Identifier (LEI)".
Entity Legal Forms is a code allocated to a party as described in ISO 20275 "Financial services Entity legal forms (ELF)".
Market Identifier Code. Identification of a financial market, as stipulated in the norm ISO 10383 "Codes for exchanges and market identifications".
Code allocated to a financial institution by the ISO 9362 Registration Authority as described in ISO 9362 "Banking - Banking telecommunication messages - Business identifier code (BIC)".
Data Universal Numbering System. A unique identification number provided by Dun & Bradstreet to identify an organization.
Place (including country) in which the organisation is registered. (ISO20022)
Place (including country) in which the organisation has its business activity. (ISO20022)
